                    "message": "Why?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "George Liu",
                        "email": "liuxiwei@ieisystem.com",
                        "username": "lxwinspur"
                    },
                    "message": "Because EM holds all sensor thresholds and manages them persistently (`/var/configuration/system.json`), without this patch, if the update fails in EM, the virtual sensor thresholds will not persist when reset bmc. This is a bug."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "I disagree.  We can still change the threshold for now, right?\n\nWith the code change we're just silently ignoring the request.  This seems just a s bad.\n\nThe fact we couldn't save to EM maybe is a bug, but we shouldn't react to one bug by adding another."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "George Liu",
                        "email": "liuxiwei@ieisystem.com",
                        "username": "lxwinspur"
                    },
                    "message": "Acknowledged"
                }
            ],
